Pre-Game Insights: Australia will play their next match of the 2023 World Cup against South Africa in the second semifinal, set to take place on 16 November at Eden Gardens, Kolkata.
Australia finished the group stage in third place with 7 wins in 9 matches.
South Africa finished in second place by virtue of their superior net run rate.
In their last group stage match, Australia rode on Mitchell Marsh's massive century (177*) to chase down 307 against Bangladesh in Pune.
South Africa's chasing woes in this World Cup have been well-documented.
The pitch at Eden Gardens is not always easy to bat on, so 270-280 is likely to be a challenging score here.
If South Africa can bat first and score 10-20 runs above par, they will be firmly in the driver's seat.
Any scenario that sees Australia bat first will tip the scales in their favour.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia and South Africa have faced off on 109 occasions in ODIs, with Australia winning 50 matches.
South Africa has won 55 matches against Australia in ODIs.
The match will begin at 2:00pm IST on 16 November 2023.
